Why is it horseshit about game content? When RIP hunts in NToV or Ssra (or any other zone for that matter) how are we taking away content?  Other guilds hunt these same spots, if named mobs are up in Umbral Plains, and we run up there only to find Wraith or LC or anyone for that matter killing them, we go somewhere else.  Thats what competition is.  We have about as good a shot of getting mobs in these zones as anyone else, sometimes we get em, sometimes we don't, thats how it works, but at least we have a CHANCE.  Players on our server that have progressed to the point to be able to take on Kunark dragons (mid 50ish) have NO CHANCE of competing with MB wizards.<br>
<br>
How would you feel if clerics started running around and killing VS and Phinney every time they poped because they got a new AA ablility that let em do it.  Hmmm clerics don't need anything from these mobs, but I'm sure VS and Phinney staffs are worth a bit to be sold for MQ, and hey clerics need to fund their twinks also...Yeah I realize this example is a bit far fetched, but I hope you see the point....its easy for you to sit back and justify burning these dragons over and over, but its not YOU getting cheesed outta epic drops or spells or haste items, its Random_Joe_EQPlayer_01 that is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
